runs.comm: Shahzad starts with four, a short and wide ball is cut hard and flat in front of square
plays back to a length ball, pushes it to midwicket, they think twice about the single, second time off a misfield, but decide to stay put
short and wide once more, and Shahzad launches a violent cut again, scything it behind point this time
pinned on the crease with a back of length ball, turns it to midwicket for a tight single
moves across and guides a short of a length ball to point
worked in front of square for another tight single, Shahzad may have struggled in case of a direct hit
appeal for caught behind down the leg side, called wide
moves away from short of a length, tapped to backward point
super strike, Mangal on the charge, builds enough momentum to connect hard and propel the short of a length ball over deep midwicket
cramps him with a short of a length ball around off, comes slowly off the pitch, defended
terrible ball, short and way down leg, he helps it easily past the man at short fine
tries to force this angled ball off the pads, cannot time it
fuller in to the pad, flicked to deep square
another one slides into the pads on a length as they look to deny them room, turned to deep square for one
that has flown over third man boundary, Shahzad flashes, and a thick edge zooms way on to the grass bank
looks to make room and swing hard, this is full around off, and he jams it back, could not get under it
low full toss on off, whipped to midwicket
taken by midwicket running forward as he backs away and top-edges a slog, was the free hit
straightens late from a full length, he pushes at it, thick edge races to third man, who messes a simple stop
tries to paddle a low full toss fine down leg, but this swings away, ends up quite some way outside off and he edges that away
moves away wide from short of a good length
hacks at a short of a good length ball, and slams it over extra cover, four more
full and swinging away sharply, he cannot get hold of it as he attacks it
makes a loud sound off the bat as he crunches this length ball, extra cover has done well to get low to his left and stop the rocket
full, into the pad, he tries to flick, misses
right through him, slower one does it, Mangal foxed into a loose drive, and the ball sneaks in between bat and pad
very full, he squeezes that through the covers
right up there again, nudged through midwicket
shortish, he has turned that straight to short fine leg
tosses it up a bit, he comes forward and pushes to wide long on
full and fast, he has a crack, and the ball hurries behind square leg off a thick inside edge
short, and that has been thumped over square with a thump of a pull
tries to cover drive but does not time it
short of a good length, thick inside edge into body and rolls away square on the off side
walks down the track, is not to the pitch, but nudges it square on leg for one
moves on the front foot to push it down the track, bowler moves to his right to field
comes in with the angle, worked to deep midwicket
turned to vacant midwicket, bowler runs after it, slides, keeps them to one
flat and slanted into middle, punched to wide long on
fast on middle stump line, jabbed to midwicket
comes out as he sees some flight, is not to the pitch, the ball turns, takes a thick inside edge behind square
dumped over deep midwicket boundary as Shahzad races to his fifty off 24 balls with a clean swing
and again, had set himself up on the leg side, cleared his front leg and walloped it higher and farther over long on
backs away to leg again and mows it down to long on
slog sweep, right in the gap between deep midwicket and deep square leg
moves outside off stump now and eyes the leg side, but the ball hits the pad and rolls on to the pitch
Shahzad dealing in boundaries, down the track again, gets under the ball and lifts it smoothly over long on
flatter ball as he sees him coming, works it through midwicket
turns another one through midwicket, doing it smartly now
turned behind square for one more
handles the bounce on this and cuts it down to third man
overpitched, mishit down to long on
length ball on off stump line, defended
short and wide, he goes in front of square with the cut, picks out extra cover
tapped to backward point for a tight single
hangs back in the crease with third man up, and quietly dabs it, but finds the fielder
straight to long off, Shahzad looking for the six again, hasn't quite got under this full one, and the fielder takes the mishit
drives the length ball, but straight to extra cover
into the pad on a length, turned to square leg
cramped with an angled length ball and pushes it to the bowler
full ball, he forces it to long off
walks out, stops and hits it to the sweeper
tossed up outside off, pushed down to long off
cut away to the sweeper
wide, and that has been hit flat and hard in the gap at extra cover
coming in with the angle, pushed to extra cover
full outside off, he flicks in the air with the spin over midwicket
tosses it up wide, and turns it in to beat him on the drive
leaves the crease and works it with the spin, midwicket dives to stop it
sitter dropped at deep square leg, absolute sitter, it was swept straight to him, he was bending and seemed to have it covered, and out it popped
tries the reverse sweep this time, misses one outside off
flat delivery around the line of off, turned to midwicket
length ball punched to extra cover
shortish ball holding up outside off, he pulls it past the non-striker to long on
punches it off the back foot to long on
pulls it between deep midwicket and long on for an easy two
down the track first ball of the over, goes with the spin, goes big, over deep midwicket
well down the leg side this time
worked to square leg
on the front foot to squeeze this past point
six more, that made such a sweet sound as he jumped out, they are going with the spin for the big hits and doing it nervelessly, gone over deep midwicket
takes a flatter one bowled from round the stumps and knocks it in front of square
full on the pad, flicked behind square
walks out to a length ball and pushes it to long on
takes it on the full with a couple of steps out and hits it to long on
length on middle, worked in front of square, they take on the deep fielders and rush back for the second, easily make it
pushes a good length ball down to long off, there is a misfield and two more are taken
nudges it in the air off the pad, to deep midwicket
well past short fine leg, fuller ball into the pad, and his flick is several feet to the right of the man in the ring
full, middle stump line, flicked again very neatly to deep square
short and wide, he is in the air as he gives the cut everything, beating the sweeper by a long way
uh oh, this high full toss has hit him on the thigh pad and then around the armpit, no-ball signalled right away, and a free hit too under the new rules
Shenwari clears front leg and drags the free hit through midwicket for four more
drives the length ball on the up to extra cover
absolutely pummelled that through covers, absolutely, sets himself deep in the crease, full ball arrives and is sent on its way
takes a step forward and defends a length ball
shortish ball into the body, not much lift, pulled to deep square
'we want sixer' was the demand from the fans at the ground, and Stanikzai delivers the win with an almighty blow over wide long on
